The recent Supreme Court decision in the United States allows SB8, a law that threatens women's health and rights, to remain in effect. This law includes a ban on abortion after six weeks of pregnancy and provides cash incentives for vigilantes. The article argues that it is important to protect the constitutional right recognized under Roe v. Wade by codifying it into law and passing the Women's Health Protection Act. The author emphasizes the need to continue defending women's reproductive rights.